21template <typename Next>
22class FastApiCallLoweringReducer : public Next {
23 public:
24 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(FastApiCallLowering)
25
26 OpIndex REDUCE(FastApiCall)(V<FrameState> frame_state, OpIndex data_argument,
27 V<Context> context,
28 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
29 const FastApiCallParameters* parameters) {
30 const auto& c_functions = parameters->c_functions;
31 const auto& c_signature = parameters->c_signature();
32 const int c_arg_count = c_signature->ArgumentCount();
33 DCHECK_EQ(c_arg_count, arguments.size());
34 const auto& resolution_result = parameters->resolution_result;
35
36 Label<> handle_error(this);
37 Label<Word32, Object> done(this);
38
39 OpIndex callee;
40 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> args;
41 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; ++i) {
42 // Check if this is the argument on which we need to perform overload
43 // resolution.
44 if (i == resolution_result.distinguishable_arg_index) {
45 DCHECK_GT(c_functions.size(), 1);
46 // This only happens when the FastApiCall node represents multiple
47 // overloaded functions and {i} is the index of the distinguishable
48 // argument.
49 OpIndex arg_i;
50 std::tie(callee, arg_i) = AdaptOverloadedFastCallArgument(
51 arguments[i], c_functions, resolution_result, handle_error);
52 args.push_back(arg_i);
53 } else {
54 CTypeInfo type = c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i);
55 args.push_back(AdaptFastCallArgument(arguments[i], type, handle_error));
56 }
57 }
58
59 if (c_functions.size() == 1) {
60 DCHECK(!callee.valid());
61 callee = __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(
62 c_functions[0].address, ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL));
63 }
64
65 // While adapting the arguments, we might have noticed an inconsistency that
66 // lead to unconditionally jumping to {handle_error}. If this happens, then
67 // we don't emit the call.
68 if (V8_LIKELY(!__ generating_unreachable_operations())) {
69 MachineSignature::Builder builder(
70 __ graph_zone(), 1,
71 c_arg_count + (c_signature->HasOptions() ? 1 : 0));
72 builder.AddReturn(MachineType::TypeForCType(c_signature->ReturnInfo()));
73 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; ++i) {
74 CTypeInfo type = c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i);
75 MachineType machine_type =
76 type.GetSequenceType() == CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar
77 ? MachineType::TypeForCType(type)
78 : MachineType::AnyTagged();
79 builder.AddParam(machine_type);
80 }
81
82 OpIndex stack_slot;
83 if (c_signature->HasOptions()) {
84 const int kAlign = alignof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions);
85 const int kSize = sizeof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions);
86 // If this check fails, you've probably added new fields to
87 // v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, which means you'll need to write code
88 // that initializes and reads from them too.
89 static_assert(kSize == sizeof(uintptr_t) * 3);
90 stack_slot = __ StackSlot(kSize, kAlign);
91
92 // fallback = 0
93 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, __ Word32Constant(0),
94 MemoryRepresentation::Int32(),
95 offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, fallback));
96 // data = data_argument
97 OpIndex data_argument_to_pass = __ AdaptLocalArgument(data_argument);
98 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, data_argument_to_pass,
99 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
100 offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, data));
101 // wasm_memory = 0
102 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, __ IntPtrConstant(0),
103 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
104 offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, wasm_memory));
105
106 args.push_back(stack_slot);
107 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
108 }
109
110 // Build the actual call.
111 const TSCallDescriptor* call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
112 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), builder.Build(),
113 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState),
114 CanThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
115 OpIndex c_call_result = WrapFastCall(call_descriptor, callee, frame_state,
116 context, base::VectorOf(args));
117
118 Label<> trigger_exception(this);
119
120 V<Object> exception =
121 __ Load(__ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(
122 IsolateAddressId::kExceptionAddress, isolate_)),
123 LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned(), MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
124 GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
125 exception,
126 __ HeapConstant(isolate_->factory()->the_hole_value()))),
127 trigger_exception);
128
129 V<Object> fast_call_result =
130 ConvertReturnValue(c_signature, c_call_result);
131
132 if (c_signature->HasOptions()) {
133 DCHECK(stack_slot.valid());
134 V<Word32> error = __ LoadOffHeap(
135 stack_slot, offsetof(v8::FastApiCallbackOptions, fallback),
136 MemoryRepresentation::Int32());
137 GOTO_IF(error, handle_error);
138 }
139 GOTO(done, FastApiCallOp::kSuccessValue, fast_call_result);
140 BIND(trigger_exception);
141 __ template CallRuntime<
142 typename RuntimeCallDescriptor::PropagateException>(
143 isolate_, frame_state, __ NoContextConstant(), {});
144
145 GOTO(done, FastApiCallOp::kFailureValue, __ TagSmi(0));
146 }
147
148 if (BIND(handle_error)) {
149 // We pass Tagged<Smi>(0) as the value here, although this should never be
150 // visible when calling code reacts to `kFailureValue` properly.
151 GOTO(done, FastApiCallOp::kFailureValue, __ TagSmi(0));
152 }
153
154 BIND(done, state, value);
155 return __ Tuple(state, value);
156 }
157
158 private:
159 std::pair<OpIndex, OpIndex> AdaptOverloadedFastCallArgument(
160 OpIndex argument, const FastApiCallFunctionVector& c_functions,
161 const fast_api_call::OverloadsResolutionResult& resolution_result,
162 Label<>& handle_error) {
163 Label<WordPtr, WordPtr> done(this);
164
165 for (size_t func_index = 0; func_index < c_functions.size(); ++func_index) {
166 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature = c_functions[func_index].signature;
167 CTypeInfo arg_type = c_signature->ArgumentInfo(
168 resolution_result.distinguishable_arg_index);
169
170 Label<> next(this);
171
172 // Check that the value is a HeapObject.
173 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(argument), handle_error);
174
175 switch (arg_type.GetSequenceType()) {
176 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence: {
177 CHECK_EQ(arg_type.GetType(), CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid);
178
179 // Check that the value is a JSArray.
180 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(argument);
181 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
182 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, JS_ARRAY_TYPE), next);
183
184 OpIndex argument_to_pass = __ AdaptLocalArgument(argument);
185 OpIndex target_address = __ ExternalConstant(
186 ExternalReference::Create(c_functions[func_index].address,
187 ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL));
188 GOTO(done, target_address, argument_to_pass);
189 break;
190 }
191 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsTypedArray: {
192 // Check that the value is a TypedArray with a type that matches the
193 // type declared in the c-function.
194 OpIndex stack_slot = AdaptFastCallTypedArrayArgument(
195 argument,
196 fast_api_call::GetTypedArrayElementsKind(
197 resolution_result.element_type),
198 next);
199 OpIndex target_address = __ ExternalConstant(
200 ExternalReference::Create(c_functions[func_index].address,
201 ExternalReference::FAST_C_CALL));
202 GOTO(done, target_address, stack_slot);
203 break;
204 }
205
206 default: {
207 UNREACHABLE();
208 }
209 }
210
211 BIND(next);
212 }
213 GOTO(handle_error);
214
215 BIND(done, callee, arg);
216 return {callee, arg};
217 }
218
219 template <typename T>
220 V<T> Checked(V<Tuple<T, Word32>> result, Label<>& otherwise) {
221 V<Word32> result_state = __ template Projection<1>(result);
222 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(result_state, TryChangeOp::kSuccessValue),
223 otherwise);
224 return __ template Projection<0>(result);
225 }
226
227 OpIndex AdaptFastCallArgument(OpIndex argument, CTypeInfo arg_type,
228 Label<>& handle_error) {
229 switch (arg_type.GetSequenceType()) {
230 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar: {
231 uint8_t flags = static_cast<uint8_t>(arg_type.GetFlags());
232 if (flags & static_cast<uint8_t>(CTypeInfo::Flags::kEnforceRangeBit)) {
233 switch (arg_type.GetType()) {
234 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32: {
235 auto result = __ TryTruncateFloat64ToInt32(argument);
236 return Checked(result, handle_error);
237 }
238 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32: {
239 auto result = __ TryTruncateFloat64ToUint32(argument);
240 return Checked(result, handle_error);
241 }
242 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64: {
243 auto result = __ TryTruncateFloat64ToInt64(argument);
244 return Checked(result, handle_error);
245 }
246 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64: {
247 auto result = __ TryTruncateFloat64ToUint64(argument);
248 return Checked(result, handle_error);
249 }
250 default: {
251 GOTO(handle_error);
252 return argument;
253 }
254 }
255 } else if (flags & static_cast<uint8_t>(CTypeInfo::Flags::kClampBit)) {
256 return ClampFastCallArgument(argument, arg_type.GetType());
257 } else {
258 switch (arg_type.GetType()) {
259 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value: {
260 return __ AdaptLocalArgument(argument);
261 }
262 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32: {
263 return __ TruncateFloat64ToFloat32(argument);
264 }
265 case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer: {
266 // Check that the value is a HeapObject.
267 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(argument), handle_error);
268 Label<WordPtr> done(this);
269
270 // Check if the value is null.
271 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
272 argument, __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value()))),
273 done, 0);
274
275 // Check that the value is a JSExternalObject.
276 GOTO_IF_NOT(
277 __ TaggedEqual(__ LoadMapField(argument),
278 __ HeapConstant(factory_->external_map())),
279 handle_error);
280
281 GOTO(done, __ template LoadField<WordPtr>(
282 V<HeapObject>::Cast(argument),
283 AccessBuilder::ForJSExternalObjectValue()));
284
285 BIND(done, result);
286 return result;
287 }
288 case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString: {
289 // Check that the value is a HeapObject.
290 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(argument), handle_error);
291 V<HeapObject> argument_obj = V<HeapObject>::Cast(argument);
292
293 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(argument_obj);
294 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
295
296 V<Word32> encoding = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(
297 instance_type, kStringRepresentationAndEncodingMask);
298 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(encoding, kSeqOneByteStringTag),
299 handle_error);
300
301 V<WordPtr> length_in_bytes = __ template LoadField<WordPtr>(
302 argument_obj, AccessBuilder::ForStringLength());
303 V<WordPtr> data_ptr = __ GetElementStartPointer(
304 argument_obj, AccessBuilder::ForSeqOneByteStringCharacter());
305
306 constexpr int kAlign = alignof(FastOneByteString);
307 constexpr int kSize = sizeof(FastOneByteString);
308 static_assert(kSize == sizeof(uintptr_t) + sizeof(size_t),
309 "The size of "
310 "FastOneByteString isn't equal to the sum of its "
311 "expected members.");
312 OpIndex stack_slot = __ StackSlot(kSize, kAlign);
313 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, data_ptr,
314 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
315 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, length_in_bytes,
316 MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(), sizeof(size_t));
317 static_assert(sizeof(uintptr_t) == sizeof(size_t),
318 "The string length can't "
319 "fit the PointerRepresentation used to store it.");
320 return stack_slot;
321 }
322 default: {
323 return argument;
324 }
325 }
326 }
327 }
328 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence: {
329 CHECK_EQ(arg_type.GetType(), CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid);
330
331 // Check that the value is a HeapObject.
332 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(argument), handle_error);
333
334 // Check that the value is a JSArray.
335 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(argument);
336 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
337 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, JS_ARRAY_TYPE), handle_error);
338
339 return __ AdaptLocalArgument(argument);
340 }
341 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsTypedArray: {
342 // Check that the value is a HeapObject.
343 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsSmi(argument), handle_error);
344
345 return AdaptFastCallTypedArrayArgument(
346 argument,
347 fast_api_call::GetTypedArrayElementsKind(arg_type.GetType()),
348 handle_error);
349 }
350 default: {
351 UNREACHABLE();
352 }
353 }
354 }
355
356 OpIndex ClampFastCallArgument(V<Float64> argument,
357 CTypeInfo::Type scalar_type) {
358 double min, max;
359 switch (scalar_type) {
360 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
361 min = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
362 max = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max();
363 break;
364 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
365 min = 0;
366 max = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
367 break;
368 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
369 min = kMinSafeInteger;
370 max = kMaxSafeInteger;
371 break;
372 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
373 min = 0;
374 max = kMaxSafeInteger;
375 break;
376 default:
377 UNREACHABLE();
378 }
379
380 V<Float64> clamped =
381 __ Conditional(__ Float64LessThan(min, argument),
382 __ Conditional(__ Float64LessThan(argument, max),
383 argument, __ Float64Constant(max)),
384 __ Float64Constant(min));
385
386 Label<Float64> done(this);
387 V<Float64> rounded = __ Float64RoundTiesEven(clamped);
388 GOTO_IF(__ Float64IsNaN(rounded), done, 0.0);
389 GOTO(done, rounded);
390
391 BIND(done, rounded_result);
392 switch (scalar_type) {
393 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
394 return __ ReversibleFloat64ToInt32(rounded_result);
395 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
396 return __ ReversibleFloat64ToUint32(rounded_result);
397 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
398 return __ ReversibleFloat64ToInt64(rounded_result);
399 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
400 return __ ReversibleFloat64ToUint64(rounded_result);
401 default:
402 UNREACHABLE();
403 }
404 }
405
406 OpIndex AdaptFastCallTypedArrayArgument(V<HeapObject> argument,
407 ElementsKind expected_elements_kind,
408 Label<>& bailout) {
409 V<Map> map = __ LoadMapField(argument);
410 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
411 GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ Word32Equal(instance_type, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE)),
412 bailout);
413
414 V<Word32> bitfield2 =
415 __ template LoadField<Word32>(map, AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2());
416 V<Word32> kind = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
417 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield2, Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask),
418 Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift);
419 GOTO_IF_NOT(LIKELY(__ Word32Equal(kind, expected_elements_kind)), bailout);
420
421 V<HeapObject> buffer = __ template LoadField<HeapObject>(
422 argument, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer());
423 V<Word32> buffer_bitfield = __ template LoadField<Word32>(
424 buffer, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField());
425
426 // Go to the slow path if the {buffer} was detached.
427 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(buffer_bitfield,
428 JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
429 bailout);
430
431 // Go to the slow path if the {buffer} is shared.
432 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(__ Word32BitwiseAnd(buffer_bitfield,
433 JSArrayBuffer::IsSharedBit::kMask)),
434 bailout);
435
436 // Unpack the store and length, and store them to a struct
437 // FastApiTypedArray.
438 OpIndex external_pointer =
439 __ LoadField(argument, AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayExternalPointer());
440
441 // Load the base pointer for the buffer. This will always be Smi
442 // zero unless we allow on-heap TypedArrays, which is only the case
443 // for Chrome. Node and Electron both set this limit to 0. Setting
444 // the base to Smi zero here allows the BuildTypedArrayDataPointer
445 // to optimize away the tricky part of the access later.
446 V<WordPtr> data_ptr;
447 if constexpr (JSTypedArray::kMaxSizeInHeap == 0) {
448 data_ptr = external_pointer;
449 } else {
450 V<Object> base_pointer = __ template LoadField<Object>(
451 argument, AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayBasePointer());
452 V<WordPtr> base = __ BitcastTaggedToWordPtr(base_pointer);
453 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
454 // Zero-extend Tagged_t to UintPtr according to current compression
455 // scheme so that the addition with |external_pointer| (which already
456 // contains compensated offset value) will decompress the tagged value.
457 // See JSTypedArray::ExternalPointerCompensationForOnHeapArray() for
458 // details.
459 base = __ ChangeUint32ToUintPtr(__ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(base));
460 }
461 data_ptr = __ WordPtrAdd(base, external_pointer);
462 }
463
464 V<WordPtr> length_in_bytes = __ template LoadField<WordPtr>(
465 argument, AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayLength());
466
467 // We hard-code int32_t here, because all specializations of
468 // FastApiTypedArray have the same size.
469 constexpr int kAlign = alignof(FastApiTypedArray<int32_t>);
470 constexpr int kSize = sizeof(FastApiTypedArray<int32_t>);
471 static_assert(kAlign == alignof(FastApiTypedArray<double>),
472 "Alignment mismatch between different specializations of "
473 "FastApiTypedArray");
474 static_assert(kSize == sizeof(FastApiTypedArray<double>),
475 "Size mismatch between different specializations of "
476 "FastApiTypedArray");
477 static_assert(
478 kSize == sizeof(uintptr_t) + sizeof(size_t),
479 "The size of "
480 "FastApiTypedArray isn't equal to the sum of its expected members.");
481 OpIndex stack_slot = __ StackSlot(kSize, kAlign);
482 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, length_in_bytes,
483 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
484 __ StoreOffHeap(stack_slot, data_ptr, MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(),
485 sizeof(size_t));
486 static_assert(sizeof(uintptr_t) == sizeof(size_t),
487 "The buffer length can't "
488 "fit the PointerRepresentation used to store it.");
489 return stack_slot;
490 }

492 V<Object> ConvertReturnValue(const CFunctionInfo* c_signature,
493 OpIndex result) {
494 switch (c_signature->ReturnInfo().GetType()) {
495 case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
496 return __ HeapConstant(factory_->undefined_value());
497 case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
498 static_assert(sizeof(bool) == 1, "unsupported bool size");
499 return __ ConvertWord32ToBoolean(
500 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(result, __ Word32Constant(0xFF)));
501 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
502 return __ ConvertInt32ToNumber(result);
503 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
504 return __ ConvertUint32ToNumber(result);
505 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64: {
506 CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation repr =
507 c_signature->GetInt64Representation();
508 if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
509 return __ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
510 result, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kBigInt,
511 RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
512 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
513 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
514 } else if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber) {
515 return __ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
516 result, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber,
517 RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
518 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
519 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
520 } else {
521 UNREACHABLE();
522 }
523 }
524 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64: {
525 CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation repr =
526 c_signature->GetInt64Representation();
527 if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
528 return __ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
529 result, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kBigInt,
530 RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
531 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kUnsigned,
532 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
533 } else if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber) {
534 return __ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
535 result, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber,
536 RegisterRepresentation::Word64(),
537 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kUnsigned,
538 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero);
539 } else {
540 UNREACHABLE();
541 }
542 }
543 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
544 return __ ConvertFloat64ToNumber(
545 __ ChangeFloat32ToFloat64(result),
546 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero);
547 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
548 return __ ConvertFloat64ToNumber(
549 result, CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero);
550 case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
551 return BuildAllocateJSExternalObject(result);
552 case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
553 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
554 case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
555 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
556 UNREACHABLE();
557 case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
558 return __ ConvertFloat64ToNumber(
559 __ ChangeInt64ToFloat64(result),
560 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero);
561 }
562 }
563
564 V<HeapObject> BuildAllocateJSExternalObject(V<WordPtr> pointer) {
565 Label<HeapObject> done(this);
566
567 // Check if the pointer is a null pointer.
568 GOTO_IF(__ WordPtrEqual(pointer, 0), done,
569 __ HeapConstant(factory_->null_value()));
570
571 Uninitialized<HeapObject> external =
572 __ Allocate(JSExternalObject::kHeaderSize, AllocationType::kYoung);
573 __ InitializeField(external, AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
574 __ HeapConstant(factory_->external_map()));
575 V<FixedArray> empty_fixed_array =
576 __ HeapConstant(factory_->empty_fixed_array());
577 __ InitializeField(external, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHash(),
578 empty_fixed_array);
579 __ InitializeField(external, AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(),
580 empty_fixed_array);
581
582#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
583 OpIndex isolate_ptr =
584 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::isolate_address(isolate_));
585 MachineSignature::Builder builder(__ graph_zone(), 1, 2);
586 builder.AddReturn(MachineType::Uint32());
587 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
588 builder.AddParam(MachineType::Pointer());
589 OpIndex allocate_and_initialize_young_external_pointer_table_entry =
590 __ ExternalConstant(
591 ExternalReference::
592 allocate_and_initialize_young_external_pointer_table_entry());
593 auto call_descriptor =
594 Linkage::GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(__ graph_zone(), builder.Build());
595 OpIndex handle =
596 __ Call(allocate_and_initialize_young_external_pointer_table_entry,
597 {isolate_ptr, pointer},
598 TSCallDescriptor::Create(call_descriptor, CanThrow::kNo,
599 __ graph_zone()));
600 __ InitializeField(
601 external, AccessBuilder::ForJSExternalObjectPointerHandle(), handle);
602#else
603 __ InitializeField(external, AccessBuilder::ForJSExternalObjectValue(),
604 pointer);
605#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
606 GOTO(done, __ FinishInitialization(std::move(external)));
607
608 BIND(done, result);
609 return result;
610 }
611
612 OpIndex WrapFastCall(const TSCallDescriptor* descriptor, OpIndex callee,
613 V<FrameState> frame_state, V<Context> context,
614 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments) {
615 // CPU profiler support.
616 OpIndex target_address = __ ExternalConstant(
617 ExternalReference::fast_api_call_target_address(isolate_));
618 __ StoreOffHeap(target_address, __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(callee),
619 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
620
621 OpIndex context_address = __ ExternalConstant(
622 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate_));
623
624 __ StoreOffHeap(context_address, __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(context),
625 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
626
627 // Create the fast call.
628 OpIndex result = __ Call(callee, frame_state, arguments, descriptor);
629
630 // Reset the CPU profiler target address.
631 __ StoreOffHeap(target_address, __ IntPtrConstant(0),
632 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
633
634#if DEBUG
635 // Reset the context again after the call, to make sure nobody is using the
636 // leftover context in the isolate.
637 __ StoreOffHeap(context_address,
638 __ WordPtrConstant(Context::kInvalidContext),
639 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr());
640#endif
641
642 return result;
643 }
644
645 Isolate* isolate_ = __ data() -> isolate();
646 Factory* factory_ = isolate_->factory();
647};
